seqhax
------------------------------------------
A collection of (mostly C) programs that are vaguely useful for sequence
analysis.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libgomp1-13.4.0-1
  libgzstream1-1.5+git20171107-1bl1
  libhts3-1.23.1-1bl1
  libqes0-0.2.8-1bl2
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  python39-3.9.16-1
  zlib0-1.3.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libgzstream-devel-1.5+git20171107-1bl1
  libhts-devel-1.23.1-1bl1
  libqes-devel-0.2.8-1bl2
  ninja-1.13.2-1
  python39-3.9.16-1
  zlib-devel-1.3.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/kdm9/seqhax

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/kdm9/seqhax/archive/refs/tags/0.8.10.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack seqhax-0.8.10-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./seqhax-0.8.10-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/seqhax-0.8.10-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/seqhax-0.8.10-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(seqhax)
  /usr/bin/htshax.exe
  /usr/bin/pecheck-wrapper.py
  /usr/bin/seqhax.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/seqhax.README
  /usr/share/doc/seqhax/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/seqhax/README.md

